Gestalt psychology emphasizes the importance of the whole over the parts, and the interaction of the whole with the environment. It also emphasizes the importance of the unconscious and the role of the individual in shaping their own perception and behavior. Today, gestalt psychology is part of the broader field of cognitive psychology, which studies the mental processes that underlie perception, attention, memory, and other cognitive functions.
